HEADWORD: Taeping
<hw>Tae"ping"</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Chin. <ets>t'aip'ing</ets> great
peace.]</ety> <fld>(Chinese Hist.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to or
designating a dynasty with which one Hung-Siu-Chuen, a half-religious,
half-political enthusiast, attempted to supplant the Manchu dynasty by
the <col><b>Taiping rebellion</b></col>, incited by him in 1850 and
suppressed by General Gordon about 1864.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

